JOHANNESBURG - South Africans have been asked to help Miss SA Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters grab the Miss Universe crown at the competition on Sunday, November 26 in Las Vegas. Pre-voting for the pageant has already opened and will close on November 25.  Fans will also get an opportunity to vote during the live broadcast for each round of the competition.  VOTING IS OPEN!If I'm your next Miss Universe you can vote by following this link: https://t.co/mcELmoxHR1#missuniverse #southafrica pic.twitter.com/vaXfGQgYMN South Africans can cast their ballots by going to Vote.MissUniverse.com. Each person can vote up to 10 times a day. Fans can also vote on Twitter using the hashtags #MissUniverse and #SouthAfrica. Retweets will count towards the final tally. The competition will be broadcast live on Vuzu (DStv Channel 116) at 05:00 (CAT). We grow when we face challenges. I overcame mine by empowering my fellow South African woman. -- @missuniverse #missuniverse #southafrica pic.twitter.com/VD7wQm8IJc GALLERY: Highlights from the 2017 Miss World Pageant eNCA